The paper deals with training deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves modifying the kernel size and input image resolution, which is related to network architecture (cs.AI) and optimization techniques (cs.NE). The paper also mentions using the ImageNet dataset, which is commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision research.
